Module Simulator
Package kin.model

Class ServoModel

java.lang.Object
kin.model.ComponentModel
kin.model.ServoModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
FixSidePartModel, TailSidePartModel
public class ServoModel
extends ComponentModel
implements TailSidePartModel, FixSidePartModel

A Servo that is able to control a certain angle in the x-y-plane. An angle of 0 means: x-direction, π/2 means: y-direction, i.e. angle go counter-clockwise.

A servo may also go 'inverse'. Then the given angle, min. and max. angles are counted in opposite direction.
Author:
Jörg Roth (Joerg.Roth@Wireless-earth.org)

  • Constructor Details

    • ServoModel

      public ServoModel​(double minFlexibleAngle, double maxFlexibleAngle, double defaultFlexibleAngle, double defaultRadPerSeconds, boolean flexibleSpeed, double minFlexibleSpeed, double maxFlexibleSpeed)
      Create a Servo.
      Parameters:
      minFlexibleAngle - minimal possible angle value to control in radians
      maxFlexibleAngle - maximum possible angle value to control in radians
      defaultFlexibleAngle - default angle value to control (i.e. the value, when the simulation starts up before any explicit setting) in radians
      defaultRadPerSeconds - servo speed in radians per second – either the fix speed or the default flexible speed
      flexibleSpeed - is the servo able to modify the servo speed?
      minFlexibleSpeed - minimum flexible speed, if flexible speed is supported, Double.NaN otherwise
      maxFlexibleSpeed - maximum flexible speed, if flexible speed is supported, Double.NaN otherwise
